OBhelper - A project written in bash to do what obmenu used to do
Started 29 August 2021
Elizabeth Mills

Structure of the existing code as at 10th October 2021
-----------------------------------------------------
Global variables:
Gnumber=0             For returning integers from functions
Gstring="y"           For returning strings from functions
declare -a OBfile     Array to hold the entire menu.xml file

Working files:
menu.xml
display.obh
temp.obh

# ---------- obh.sh - Main module ---------
Main() {
SaveToFile()
ShowMessage()  Show a message in a pop-up terminal window
Debug()

# ---------- obh2.sh - Preparation functions ---------
MakeFile()     						Prepare the display file using functions in this module
FormatRecordForDisplay()	Amalgamate data from each record into one line for display
Indentation()        			Indentation according to menu level

# ---------- obh3.sh - Input and output functions ---------
ShowList()     Use Yad to display the file contents in a listbox and enable user actions
EditObject()   Choose action based on type of object
FormatItem()   Load, edit and save the record
FormatMenu()   Load, edit and save the record
FormatSep()    Load, edit and save the separator

# ---------- obh4.sh - Add records ---------
AddItem()				
AddMenu()				
AddSeparator()	
CheckMenuID()		

# ---------- obh5.sh - Move up and move down ---------
MoveUp()       TODO
